Company Overview of Equinox Institutional Asset Management, LP



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Equinox Institutional Asset Management, LP is a privately owned hedge fund sponsor. The firm also acts as a commodity trading advisor and commodity pool operator. It primarily provides its services to non-profit organizations. The firm manages client specific hedge fund portfolios. It also manages an equity fund for its clients. The firm invests in alternative investment markets. It’s primary investments comprise of hedge funds and future contracts. The firm combines equity long/short, arbitrage, and trading strategies for its investments. It employs a combination of qualitative and quantitative analysis to make its investments. The firm was founded in October 2002 and is based in Princeton,...
Equinox Institutional Asset Management, LP is a privately owned hedge fund sponsor. The firm also acts as a commodity trading advisor and commodity pool operator. It primarily provides its services to non-profit organizations. The firm manages client specific hedge fund portfolios. It also manages an equity fund for its clients. The firm invests in alternative investment markets. It’s primary investments comprise of hedge funds and future contracts. The firm combines equity long/short, arbitrage, and trading strategies for its investments. It employs a combination of qualitative and quantitative analysis to make its investments. The firm was founded in October 2002 and is based in Princeton, New Jersey. Equinox Institutional Asset Management, LP operates as a subsidiary of Equinox Financial Group, LLC.
Detailed Description


