Equinox Institutional Asset Management LP



 OVERVIEW



Date Founded


2003




Headquarters


47 Hulfish Street, Suite 510, Princeton, NJ 08542-3713




Employees (Worldwide)


12




Industries


Investment Services & Portfolio Management




Company Description


Equinox Institutional Asset Management specializes in the construction, implementation and monitoring of multi-manager hedge fund portfolios and managed futures strategies. The firm provides discretionary and non-discretionary investment advisory services to institutions and other qualified investment groups. They provide advice on the allocation of assets to third-party investment managers that use a broad range of investment strategies in the alternative investment space including Equity Long/Short, Arbitrage and Trading. The Equinox Alternative Strategy Platform is a platform of single Commodity Trading Advisor (CTA) program alternative investment mutual funds. The platform presents liquid and transparent alternative investment strategies, and a broader application of Equinox’s capabilities to serve some investors.Equinox serves as the investment advisor for Equinox MutualHedge Futures Strategy Fund, a 1940 Act Fund, offered through Northern Lights Fund Trust, a mutual fund family that offers separate investment portfolios. The fund seeks to achieve capital appreciation in both bull and bear equity markets with an annual volatility that is generally lower than the volatility experienced by the S&P 500 Index. The fund invests in a combination of derivatives and fixed income securities. Equinox also serves as the investment advisor for Equinox EquityHedge US Strategy Fund, a 1940 Act Fund that seeks to provide exposure to broad-based US equity indices while employing a hedging strategy to potentially enhance returns and dampen risk during periods of equity market stress.




Website


http://www.equinoxfunds.com






